  44:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) Initialize the related GPIO clocks
  45:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) Configure Ethernet pinout
  46:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) Configure Ethernet NVIC interrupt (in Interrupt mode)
  47:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  48:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****       (#) Ethernet data reception is asynchronous, so call the following API
  49:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           to start the listening mode:
  50:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) HAL_ETH_Start():
  51:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****                This API starts the MAC and DMA transmission and reception process,
  52:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****                without enabling end of transfer interrupts, in this mode user
  53:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****                has to poll for data reception by calling HAL_ETH_ReadData()
  54:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) HAL_ETH_Start_IT():
  55:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****                This API starts the MAC and DMA transmission and reception process,
  56:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****                end of transfer interrupts are enabled in this mode,
  57:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****                HAL_ETH_RxCpltCallback() will be executed when an Ethernet packet is received
  58:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  59:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****       (#) When data is received user can call the following API to get received data:
  60:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) HAL_ETH_ReadData(): Read a received packet
  61:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  62:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****       (#) For transmission path, two APIs are available:
  63:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****          (##) HAL_ETH_Transmit(): Transmit an ETH frame in blocking mode
  64:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****          (##) HAL_ETH_Transmit_IT(): Transmit an ETH frame in interrupt mode,
  65:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****               HAL_ETH_TxCpltCallback() will be executed when end of transfer occur
  66:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  67:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****       (#) Communication with an external PHY device:
  68:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****          (##) HAL_ETH_ReadPHYRegister(): Read a register from an external PHY
  69:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****          (##) HAL_ETH_WritePHYRegister(): Write data to an external RHY register
  70:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  71:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****       (#) Configure the Ethernet MAC after ETH peripheral initialization
  72:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) HAL_ETH_GetMACConfig(): Get MAC actual configuration into ETH_MACConfigTypeDef
  73:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****           (##) HAL_ETH_SetMACConfig(): Set MAC configuration based on ETH_MACConfigTypeDef
  74:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
