  94:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
  95:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   =============================================
  96:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
  97:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_ETH_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
  98:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
  99:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Use Function HAL_ETH_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
 100:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 101:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Function HAL_ETH_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 102:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback   : Tx Complete Callback.
 103:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback   : Rx Complete Callback.
 104:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback    : Error Callback.
 105:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) PMTCallback      : Power Management Callback
 106:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) EEECallback      : EEE Callback.
 107:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) WakeUpCallback   : Wake UP Callback
 108:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback  : MspInit Callback.
 109:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback: MspDeInit Callback.
 110:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 111:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 112:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 113:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 114:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxAllocateCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 115:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterRxAllocateCallback().
 116:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 117:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxLinkCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 118:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterRxLinkCallback().
 119:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 120:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxFreeCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 121:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterTxFreeCallback().
 122:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 123:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxPtpCallback use dedicated register callbacks:
 124:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_RegisterTxPtpCallback().
 125:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 126:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Use function HAL_ETH_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 127:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   weak function.
 128:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   HAL_ETH_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 129:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 130:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 131:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) TxCpltCallback   : Tx Complete Callback.
 132:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) RxCpltCallback   : Rx Complete Callback.
 133:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback    : Error Callback.
 134:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) PMTCallback      : Power Management Callback
 135:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) EEECallback      : EEE Callback.
 136:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) WakeUpCallback   : Wake UP Callback
 137:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback  : MspInit Callback.
 138:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback: MspDeInit Callback.
 139:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 140:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxAllocateCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
 141:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterRxAllocateCallback().
 142:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 143:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks RxLinkCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
ARM GAS  /tmp/cc7Yyyw7.s 			page 4


 144:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterRxLinkCallback().
 145:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 146:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxFreeCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
 147:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterTxFreeCallback().
 148:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 149:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   For specific callbacks TxPtpCallback use dedicated unregister callbacks:
 150:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   respectively HAL_ETH_UnRegisterTxPtpCallback().
 151:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 152:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   By default, after the HAL_ETH_Init and when the state is HAL_ETH_STATE_RESET
 153:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 154:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   examples HAL_ETH_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_ETH_RxCpltCallback().
 155:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 156:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   reset to the legacy weak function in the HAL_ETH_Init/ HAL_ETH_DeInit only when
 157:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 158:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   if not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_ETH_Init/ HAL_ETH_DeInit
 159:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 160:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 161:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_ETH_STATE_READY state only.
 162:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 163:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   in HAL_ETH_STATE_READY or HAL_ETH_STATE_RESET state,
 164:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 165:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 166:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   using HAL_ETH_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_ETH_DeInit
 167:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   or HAL_ETH_Init function.
 168:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c **** 
 169:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_ETH_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 170:../../Drivers/STM32H7xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h7xx_hal_eth.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
